### API Test File for Report Generator
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension
### Click "Send Request" above each request to execute

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json

### ===========================================
### Authentication API
### ===========================================

### 1. User Registration
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Taro Yamada",
  "email": "yamada@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Register Another User (for testing)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Hanako Sato",
  "email": "sato@example.com",
  "password": "password456"
}

### 3. Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "yamada@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 4. Get Current User Information (JWT required)
# Paste the token obtained from login above
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### ===========================================
### Error Case Tests
### ===========================================

### 5. Validation Error - Name too short
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "A",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 6. Validation Error - Password too short
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test2@example.com",
  "password": "12345"
}

### 7. Validation Error - Invalid email address
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 8. Duplicate Error - Existing email address
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Jiro Yamada",
  "email": "yamada@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 9. Login Error - Wrong password
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "yamada@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

### 10. Login Error - Non-existent user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "notexist@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}
